ir dual operators,\nacting from $M^{(k)}(X)$ into $M^{(n)}(X)$, satisfy\n$(\\omega)_n=\\sum_{k=1}^n\\mathbf{s}(n,k)^*\\omega^{\\otimes k}$ and\n$\\omega^{\\otimes n}=\\sum_{k=1}^n\\mathbf{S}(n,k)^*(\\omega)_k$, respectively. We\nderive combinatorial properties of the Stirling operators, present their\nconnections with a generalization of the Poisson point process and with the\nWick ordering under the canonical commutation relations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Jul 2020 11:05:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Jul 2020 10:49:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 17 Aug 2020 11:17:39 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 18 Aug 2020 08:47:24 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 19 May 2021 10:34:00 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 16 Sep 2021 10:58:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-24"}
